Objective

To identify all the actors who interact with the Blood Bank Management System (BBMS) either directly or indirectly.

Identified Actors
1. Blood Bank Administrator

Description:
The Blood Bank Administrator is the primary actor responsible for managing the overall system. This actor controls donor records, blood inventory, user accounts, blood request approvals, and report generation.

Type: Primary Actor

2. Hospital Staff

Description:
Hospital Staff interact with the system to check blood availability and submit blood requests for patients during emergencies or scheduled treatments.

Type: Primary Actor

3. Authorized Staff

Description:
Authorized Staff assist in daily operations such as updating donor details, adding blood units, and maintaining inventory records.

Type: Primary Actor

4. Blood Donor

Description:
The Blood Donor registers in the system to donate blood and receives notifications regarding donation eligibility and emergency requirements.

Type: Primary Actor

5. System (Blood Bank Management System)

Description:
The system itself acts as a secondary actor by automatically validating data, generating alerts, managing authentication, and maintaining records.

Type: Secondary Actor

| Actor                    | Role                                 | Actor Type |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------ | ---------- |
| Blood Bank Administrator | System management and control        | Primary    |
| Hospital Staff           | Blood request and availability check | Primary    |
| Authorized Staff         | Inventory and donor updates          | Primary    |
| Blood Donor              | Donation and notifications           | Primary    |
| System                   | Automation and validation            | Secondary  |
